The bus was on its way to an ANC event. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Six people died in a bus accident in Limpopo on Sunday. The bus was en route to an ANC event. Limpopo Health MEC, Phophi Ramathuba was one of the first people on the scene. Ramathuba says the accident happened near Ga-Sekgopo. "It is indeed a sad day for us as the people of Limpopo. We certified that six people died on the scene." Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula sent his condolences to the families of the victims.   According to Mbalula, the driver lost control of the bus. Mbalula adds that an investigation into the exact cause of the accident is underway. Watch the full interview with Limpopo Health MEC, Phophi Ramathuba in the video above.